RF Excitation Predictability- 

     Pbox-Generated 90-Degree Pulses

The Pbox utility in VNMR permits direct
calculation of pulse parameters from a
single power/pulse width calibration.
Here, 4000 Hz bandwidth 90-degree pulses
are calculated directly from the proton
calibration values for a wide variety
of shapes:

                square(rectangular)
                hs     (hyperbolic secant)
                av90   (Abramovich/Vega universal rotor)
                Q5     (Bodenhausen (gaussian cascade)
                eburp2 (Geen/Freeman tophat)
                hgaus  (half gaussian)
                gaus90 (gaussian)
                sinc   (sinc: sinx/x)
                sneeze (Nuzillard/Freeman tophat)

Pbox output includes the shape, power and width.
The resulting NMR responses should be identical. 

